{
  "version": 1,
  "notes": [
    "Spice terms are a sharper, more human-readable layer on top of the sober negative-signal lexicon.",
    "Use these for review leads and for the narrower swear index timeline.",
    "Matches are still review leads. Pasted quotes or long specs can contain these words without being a direct emotional turn.",
    "The swearing group intentionally includes common variants people may use beyond this user's exact phrasing so the audit can be reused.",
    "swear_index_excluded_terms are still matched for review, but do not count in the visible swear index unless another stronger term also matches the same message."
  ],
